# Datadog MCP
Use `mcp-cli` with `dd-auth` to access Datadog MCP.

Config:
- Config file: `~/.config/mcp/mcp_servers.json`
- MCP URL: `https://mcp.datadoghq.com/api/unstable/mcp-server/mcp`
- Prod server: `datadog-prod`
- Staging server: `datadog-staging`

Auth and routing:
- Prod org2: `dd-auth --domain app.datadoghq.com -- ...`
- Staging org 197728 ddstaging: `dd-auth --domain ddstaging.datadoghq.com -- ...`
- The MCP URL is the same for prod and staging; `dd-auth --domain` selects the Datadog org.

Choose prod vs staging from the cluster/datacenter name:
- Use staging for cluster/datacenter names containing staging indicators, especially:
  - `*.staging.dog`
  - `*.ddbuild.staging.dog`
  - `stormeagle.us1.staging.dog`
- Use prod for production cluster/datacenter names, especially:
  - `*.prod.dog`
  - `*.ddbuild.io`
  - `app.datadoghq.com` links
- If the environment is ambiguous, ask before querying.

Discovery:
```fish
MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain app.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli info datadog-prod
MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain ddstaging.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli info datadog-staging
MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain app.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli info datadog-prod search_datadog_logs
MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain app.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli info datadog-prod get_datadog_metric
```

Common prod calls:
```fish
MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain app.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli call datadog-prod search_datadog_logs '{
  "query": "service:my-service",
  "from": "now-15m",
  "to": "now",
  "max_tokens": 4000,
  "telemetry": {"dd_mcp_source": "pi"}
}'

MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain app.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli call datadog-prod get_datadog_metric '{
  "queries": [{"name": "query1", "data_source": "metrics", "query": "avg:system.cpu.user{*}"}],
  "from": "now-15m",
  "to": "now",
  "max_tokens": 4000,
  "telemetry": {"dd_mcp_source": "pi"}
}'
```

Common staging calls:
```fish
MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain ddstaging.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli call datadog-staging search_datadog_logs '{
  "query": "kube_cluster_name:stormeagle.us1.staging.dog",
  "from": "now-15m",
  "to": "now",
  "max_tokens": 4000,
  "telemetry": {"dd_mcp_source": "pi"}
}'

MCP_NO_DAEMON=1 dd-auth --domain ddstaging.datadoghq.com -- mcp-cli call datadog-staging search_datadog_metrics '{
  "tag_filter": "kube_cluster_name:stormeagle.us1.staging.dog",
  "max_tokens": 4000,
  "telemetry": {"dd_mcp_source": "pi"}
}'
```

Rules:
- Prefer read-only tools.
- Do not create or edit notebooks or dashboards unless explicitly asked.
- Use narrow time windows first, usually `now-15m` to `now` or the user-provided incident window.
- Include `max_tokens` on search/aggregate calls.
- Include telemetry: `{"dd_mcp_source": "pi"}`.
- Use stdin/heredocs for complex JSON to avoid shell quoting issues.
- Never print or persist `DD_API_KEY` or `DD_APP_KEY`.
